content.description: Climb a number of problems along rock band that faces to the south.  Many good problems that area little harder, but mostly easy and moderate.  Another good area to check out if you have time and are in need to add some FA's to Rib Mt.  Can be dirty due to lack of traffic.
content.location: From parking area, head south-east into woods.  You will find rock all over.  Most obvious lines are good and clean, but many yet to be done

content.description: A couple variations to this boulder and nothing tricky.  Climb all around it for some easy fun.
content.location: Walk west from Low Wing Loaded.  Short boulder is a short boulder downhill past South facing rock band, with cool features to it.

content.description: Play around on all the features right across from the parking spot.  No real names and grades to this spot just some fun.  Can be dirty due to lack of traffic.
content.location: Across the road from parking spot.

content.description: SDS and throw slap up left arete.  Mantle straight over lip.
content.location: Cool, short and sharp overhanging block a few minutes walk from parking.  From parking spot, hike south-east into woods and look for a boulder standing alone.  Problem faces east so it's not easy to see, just keep looking.

content.description: Scattered problems worth checking out.  Mostly easier and not as clean, due to lack of traffic.  Good place for beginners to go and kick around.
